::Spears::

Her trainer side was seeing some difficulty with this.  The self 
preservation of the program dictated that she not go into stasis 
lock.  But she had no choise at this point.

Right then, her body shook as the maximal program returned and took 
over.  She had little knowlage of the discussion about going into 
stasis.  She simply kept walking, and didn't reply.  But she was 
starting to get worried about these momentary black outs.  While her 
trainer side stayed ever alert to what was going on. But she 
remembered being told that she was going tothe Cybertron Fire just to 
get checked out.

"So how is Cybertron Fire. Hope everyone back there is ok."
